   "source": [
    "# Import library here\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "9c3c5213",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_train_clean = pd.read_csv(\"../../data/processed/01.3/accidents_advance_clean.csv\")\n",
    "\n",
    "df_train_clean.head(10)"
    ]
    },
    {
    "cell_type": "markdown",
    "id": "eda-city-title",
    "metadata": {},
    "source": [
    "## 1. Top 10 Cities with Most Accidents"
    ]
    },
    {
    "cell_type": "code",
    "id": "eda-city-plot",
    "metadata": {},
    "outputs": [],
    "source": [
    "city_counts = df_train_clean['City'].value_counts().head(10)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "city_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='skyblue')\n",
    "plt.title('Top 10 Cities with Most Accidents', fontsize=15)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('City', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Number of Accidents', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "plt.show()"
    ]
    },
    {
    "cell_type": "markdown",
    "id": "eda-suggestions",
    "metadata": {},
    "source": [
    "## Other Interesting EDA Suggestions\n",
    "\n",
    "Here are some other analyses that could provide valuable insights:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Time-based Analysis**:\n",
    "   - **Accidents by Hour**: Analyze if rush hours (7-9 AM, 4-6 PM) correlate with higher accident counts.\n",
    "   - **Accidents by Day of Week**: Compare weekday vs. weekend patterns.\n",
    "   - **Monthly Trends**: Identify seasonal peaks (e.g., winter weather impacts).\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Environmental & Weather Analysis**:\n",
    "   - **Weather Condition vs. Severity**: Do certain weather groups (e.g., Snow, Rain) lead to higher severity accidents?\n",
    "   - **Visibility & Temperature**: Correlation between low visibility or extreme temperatures and accident frequency.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **Road Features Impact**:\n",
    "   - **Traffic Signals, Junctions, and Crossings**: How many accidents happen near these features?\n",
    "\n",
    "4. **Geographic Distribution**:\n",
    "   - **Accidents by State**: Top states with the highest incident rates.\n",
    "   - **Severity by Region**: Does severity vary significantly between different states or counties?\n",
    "\n",
    "5. **Severity Distribution**:\n",
    "   - A general overview of the `Severity` levels to understand the balance of the dataset."
    ]
    }
